# AI Agent Configuration & Project Rules

This document outlines workspace-specific rules, skills, and behaviors that AI assistants should follow when working on the **live-scorez** repository.

## Branch Naming and Git Workflow
- When setting up new functionalities (features), **always** ensure to create a new branch.
- Use the prefix `feat/` followed by the name of the feature: `feat/(name of feature)`.
  - *Example*: For setting up the database/ORM, use `feat/database-orm-setup`.
- For bug fixes, use `fix/(description)`.
- For other tasks, use `chore/` or `refactor/`.
- Ensure all PRs follow the structure defined in [pull_request.md](file:///c:/Users/coded/Desktop/live-scorez/pull_request.md).

## Technology Stack & Best Practices
- **Language**: TypeScript
- **Framework**: ExpressJS
- **Database**: Neon (PostgreSQL)
- **ORM**: Drizzle ORM
